West Pokot Governor John Lonyanga?Puo Says The First Phase Of Distributing Food To Landslide, Mudslides, And Floods Victims In The County Is Successful And The Second Phase Of Re?Housing The Victims Is Currently Underway. According To Devolution Cs, Eugene Wamalwa, Who Visited          Makutona Town On A Food Distribution Mission, The Government Will Distribute 4,000 Pieces Of Iron Sheets To Families Affected By The Tragedy. The Authorities Are Collaborating With Red Cross Officials To Identify And Distribute Building Materials To Displaced Victims At Parua, Nyarkulian And Paroo Camps.